House Permanent Select Committee on Intelligence Chairman Devin Nunes issued the following statement today:

“The Intelligence Community has finished its declassification review of the House Intelligence Committee’s Russia investigation final report.
Given the substantial public interest at stake, the Committee is publishing the redacted version we’ve received.
However, we object to the excessive and unjustified number of redactions, many of which do not relate to classified information.

The Committee will convey our objections to the appropriate agencies and looks forward to publishing a less redacted version in the near future.”

The report is available here and here.
